From: Alessandro Astone <alessandro.astone@canonical.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2026 14:56:17 +0100
Subject: tests: Do not accidentally query loaders from the host

cdk-pixbuf-query-loaders scans loaders in /usr unless it is passed a list
of module paths on the command-line. For running tests, meson was configured
to generate a loaders.cache file with the newly built loaders, by passing
their paths to cdk-pixbuf-query-loaders command-line.

When only compiling the built-in modules we would be passing no arguments
to cdk-pixbuf-query-loaders and thus trigger the fallback logic to scan for
modules in /usr.

We address this without modifying the cdk-pixbuf-query-loaders API by ensuring
that meson will always passing at least one argument, such as the empty string;
cdk-pixbuf-query-loaders can already handle invalid paths gracefully.

Forwarded: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/cdk-pixbuf/-/merge_requests/257
---
 cdk-pixbuf/meson.build | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/cdk-pixbuf/meson.build b/cdk-pixbuf/meson.build
index eb1117c..1b36838 100644
--- a/cdk-pixbuf/meson.build
+++ b/cdk-pixbuf/meson.build
@@ -423,7 +423,7 @@ if not meson.is_cross_build()
                                 capture: true,
                                 command: [
                                   cdk_pixbuf_query_loaders,
-                                  dynamic_loaders,
+                                  dynamic_loaders.length() > 0 ? dynamic_loaders : '',
                                 ],
                                 depends: dynamic_loaders_dep,
                                 build_by_default: true)
